title: PPPP’s Ubaid Ullah wins PB-44 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) Ubaid Ullah has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-44, Quetta-VII by securing 7,125 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was national Party Mir Atta Muhammad Bangulzai who bagged 6,385 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 31.97 per cent.
